    {
      "id": "line-0",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "You are a professor of physics at the university of Oxford.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-1",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "You're a senior advisor at the European Organization for Nuclear Research.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-2",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "You also seem to tour the globe tirelessly.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-3",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "How do you manage to do it all?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-4",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Oh, well.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 2,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-5",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "I just love what I do.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 6,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-6",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "I'm extremely fortunate to have this life, doing what I love doing.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-7",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "Professor, what exactly is your goal?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 6,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-8",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "Why do you do all of this?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-9",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Well, as you said, I'm a professor of physics at the university of Oxford.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-10",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "This means I do research in physics, and I teach physics at the university.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-11",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "I'm also a senior advisor at CERN, the European Organization for Nuclear Research.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-12",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "That involves advising on various aspects of the research being done at CERN.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-13",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "And I also have a weekly TV show called \"The Universe\" which is broadcast in several countries.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-14",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "You mentioned teaching.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 3,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-15",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "What do you enjoy most about teaching?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-16",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "I love interacting with students.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 5,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-17",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "It's a great way to keep my mind sharp.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-18",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "When you have to explain something to someone else, you really have to understand it yourself.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 16,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-19",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "So teaching helps me to better understand the subjects I'm researching.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-20",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "And what about your research?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 5,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-21",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "What are you currently working on?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 6,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-22",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "I'm working on several projects.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 5,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-23",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "One of them is about the origin of the universe.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-24",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "We're trying to understand how the universe began and how it has evolved over time.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-25",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Another project is about dark matter and dark energy, which make up most of the universe.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 16,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-26",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "We still don't know what they are, but we're trying to find out.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-27",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "It sounds fascinating.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 3,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-28",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "But how do you make new scientific breakthroughs possible?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-29",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Well, I think it's a combination of things.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-30",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "First, you need to have a good understanding of the existing research.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-31",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Then you need to be curious and ask questions.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-32",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "You also need to be persistent and not give up when things get difficult.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-33",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "And finally, you need to collaborate with other scientists.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-34",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Science is a team effort.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 5,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-35",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "Q1.",
      "text": "Why does the woman say she can be so energetic?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-36",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "Q2.",
      "text": "What has the woman been engaged in?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-37",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "Q3.",
      "text": "What does the woman say about the benefit teaching brings to her?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-38",
      "sectionId": "conversation-1",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 1",
      "speaker": "Q4.",
      "text": "How does the woman say new scientific breakthroughs can be made possible?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-39",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "Do you think dreams have special meanings?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-40",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "No, I don't think they do.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 6,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-41",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Dreams are just random thoughts and images that our brains produce while we're sleeping.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-42",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "But some people believe that dreams can predict the future or give us insights into our subconscious.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-43",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "I think that's just superstition.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 5,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-44",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "There's no scientific evidence to support those claims.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-45",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Dreams are simply a byproduct of the brain's activity during sleep.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-46",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "Exactly.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 1,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-47",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "People do all sorts of crazy things because of their irrational feelings.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-48",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "But in fact, some psychologists believe that our dreams are the result of our emotions and memories from that day.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 20,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-49",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "I think it was Sigmund Freud who said that children's dreams were usually simple representations of their wishes, things they wished would happen.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 23,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-50",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "But in adults, dreams are much more complicated reflections of their more sophisticated sentiments.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-51",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Isn't it interesting how psychologists try to understand using the scientific method something as strange as dreams?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-52",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "It is.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 2,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-53",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "But there's still a lot we don't know about the brain.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-54",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "For example, why do we dream?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 6,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-55",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "What purpose do dreams serve?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 5,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-56",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Some researchers believe that dreaming helps us to process and consolidate memories.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-57",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Others think that it's a way for the brain to sort through and eliminate unnecessary information.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 16,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-58",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "That makes sense.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 3,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-59",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "But what about lucid dreams?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 5,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-60",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "Have you ever had a lucid dream?",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-61",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "Yes, I have.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 3,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-62",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "A lucid dream is when you're aware that you're dreaming and can control the dream.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-63",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "It's a very strange experience.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 5,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-64",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "M:",
      "text": "I've heard that some people use lucid dreaming to overcome fears or to practice skills.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-65",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "That's right.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 2,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-66",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "But it's not easy to have a lucid dream.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-67",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "W:",
      "text": "You have to train yourself to recognize when you're dreaming.",
      "type": "dialogue",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-68",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "Q5.",
      "text": "What do the speakers think of dreams?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-69",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "Q6.",
      "text": "What did Sigmund Freud say about children's dreams according to the man?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-70",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "Q7.",
      "text": "What do some researchers believe about dreaming?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-71",
      "sectionId": "conversation-2",
      "sectionTitle": "CONVERSATION 2",
      "speaker": "Q8.",
      "text": "What does the woman say about lucid dreams?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
