    },
    {
      "id": "line-73",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Scientists have identified thousands of known ant species around the world.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-74",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "And only a few of them bug humans.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-75",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Most ants live in the woods or out in nature.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-76",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "There, they keep other creatures in check, distribute seeds, and clean dead and decaying materials from the ground.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 18,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-77",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "A very small percentage of ants do harm to humans.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-78",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "But those are incredibly challenging to control.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-79",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "They are small enough to easily slip inside your house, live in colonies that number in the tens of thousands to the hundreds of thousands, and reproduce quickly.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 28,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-80",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "That makes them good at getting in and hard to kick out.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-81",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Once they settle in, these insects start affecting your home.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-82",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "In addition to biting ants, other species can cause different kinds of damage.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-83",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Some, like carpenter ants, can undermine a home's structure, while others interfere with electrical units.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-84",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Unfortunately, our homes are very attractive to ants because they provide everything the colony needs to survive: food, water, and shelter.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 21,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-85",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "So how can we prevent ants from getting into our homes?",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-86",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Most important of all, avoid giving ants any access to food, particularly sugary food, because ants have a sweet tooth.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 20,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-87",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We should also seal up any cracks or holes that ants can use to enter our homes.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-88",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Even if the cracks are tiny, ants can squeeze through them.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-89",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Additionally, keep your home clean and free of food debris.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-90",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "This will make it less attractive to ants.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-91",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "If ants have already gotten into your home, you can use baits to eliminate them.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-92",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Baits are effective because ants take the bait back to their colony, where it kills the entire colony.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 18,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-93",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "Q9.",
      "text": "What does the passage say about most ants?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-94",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "Q10.",
      "text": "What does the passage say about ants that harm humans?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-95",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "Q11.",
      "text": "Why are our homes attractive to ants according to the passage?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-96",
      "sectionId": "passage-1",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 1",
      "speaker": "Q12.",
      "text": "What can we do to prevent ants from getting into our homes?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-97",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "When John Copeland started building his tiny house on wheels, he had no idea how popular it would become.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 19,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-98",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "He built the house to live in, not to sell.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 10,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-99",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "But after posting photos of his finished home on social media, he started getting inquiries from people who wanted to buy one.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 22,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-100",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Copeland's tiny house is 120 square feet.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-101",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It has a kitchen, a bathroom, a living area, and a bedroom.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-102",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The house is built on a trailer, so it can be moved anywhere.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-103",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Copeland says that living in a tiny house has many benefits.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-104",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It's more affordable than a traditional home, and it's easier to maintain.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-105",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It also allows him to live a more minimalist lifestyle, which he says has made him happier.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 17,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-106",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "But living in a tiny house isn't for everyone.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-107",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Copeland says that you have to be willing to downsize your possessions and adjust to living in a small space.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 20,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-108",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "You also have to be prepared for the challenges of living in a tiny house, such as limited storage space and the need to be creative with your living arrangements.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 30,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-109",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Despite these challenges, Copeland says that he has no regrets about building his tiny house.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-110",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "He says that it has changed his life for the better, and he hopes that more people will consider living in tiny houses in the future.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 26,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-111",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "Q13.",
      "text": "What do we learn about John Copeland's tiny house?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-112",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "Q14.",
      "text": "What are the benefits of living in a tiny house according to Copeland?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-113",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "Q15.",
      "text": "What challenges does Copeland say people have to face when living in a tiny house?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-114",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "Q16.",
      "text": "What does Copeland say about his tiny house?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-115",
      "sectionId": "passage-2",
      "sectionTitle": "PASSAGE 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "---",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 1,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-116",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Today, I'm going to talk about social influence.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-117",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Social influence is the process by which individuals change their attitudes, beliefs, or behaviors as a result of interacting with others.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 21,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-118",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "There are many different types of social influence, including conformity, compliance, and obedience.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-119",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Conformity is when individuals change their behavior to match the behavior of others in a group.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 16,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-120",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Compliance is when individuals agree to a request from someone else.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-121",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Obedience is when individuals follow the orders of an authority figure.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-122",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Social influence can have both positive and negative effects.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-123",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "On the positive side, it can help us to learn new things, to fit in with others, and to cooperate with others.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 22,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-124",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "On the negative side, it can lead us to make bad decisions, to follow the crowd, and to obey authority figures even when they are wrong.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 26,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-125",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "One of the most famous studies on social influence is the Asch conformity experiment.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-126",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "In this experiment, participants were asked to judge the length of lines.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-127",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "They were placed in a group with other people who were actually actors.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-128",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The actors gave incorrect answers to see if the participants would conform.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-129",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The results showed that about 75% of the participants conformed at least once.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-130",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Another famous study is the Milgram obedience experiment.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-131",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "In this experiment, participants were asked to administer electric shocks to another person.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 13,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-132",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The shocks were not real, but the participants thought they were.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-133",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The results showed that most participants were willing to administer the shocks even when they thought the other person was in pain.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 22,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-134",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "These studies show that social influence is a powerful force that can affect our behavior in many ways.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 18,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-135",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It's important to be aware of social influence so that we can make better decisions and avoid being influenced in negative ways.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 22,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-136",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "Q17.",
      "text": "What is social influence according to the speaker?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-137",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "Q18.",
      "text": "What are the different types of social influence mentioned in the talk?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-138",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "Q19.",
      "text": "What does the speaker say about the positive effects of social influence?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-139",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "Q20.",
      "text": "What did the Asch conformity experiment show?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-140",
      "sectionId": "recording-1",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 1",
      "speaker": "Q21.",
      "text": "What did the Milgram obedience experiment show?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-141",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The world's oceans are facing unprecedented challenges.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 7,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-142",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Climate change, overfishing, pollution, and ocean acidification are all taking a toll on marine ecosystems.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-143",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "These challenges are interconnected and require a global response.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 9,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-144",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Climate change is causing sea levels to rise, which is threatening coastal communities and ecosystems.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-145",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It's also causing ocean temperatures to rise, which is affecting the distribution of marine species and the productivity of marine ecosystems.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 21,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-146",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Overfishing is depleting fish stocks around the world.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 8,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-147",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Many species are being caught faster than they can reproduce, which is leading to a decline in biodiversity.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 18,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-148",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Pollution from plastic, oil, and other sources is also a major problem.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-149",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Plastic pollution is particularly harmful because it can take hundreds of years to break down.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-150",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It can also be ingested by marine animals, which can cause injury or death.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-151",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "Ocean acidification is another major challenge.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 6,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-152",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It's caused by the absorption of carbon dioxide from the atmosphere.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-153",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "This is making the oceans more acidic, which is affecting the ability of marine organisms to build shells and skeletons.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 20,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-154",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "The good news is that there are things we can do to address these challenges.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 15,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-155",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We can reduce our carbon footprint to help slow climate change.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-156",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We can support sustainable fishing practices to help rebuild fish stocks.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 11,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-157",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "We can reduce our use of plastic and properly dispose of waste to help reduce pollution.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 16,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-158",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "And we can support research and innovation to help develop new technologies and solutions.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-159",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "",
      "text": "It's important that we take action now to protect our oceans for future generations.",
      "type": "narration",
      "words": 14,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
    {
      "id": "line-160",
      "sectionId": "recording-2",
      "sectionTitle": "RECORDING 2",
      "speaker": "Q22.",
      "text": "What are the challenges facing the world's oceans according to the speaker?",
      "type": "question",
      "words": 12,
      "start": 0,
      "end": 0
    },
